The paper deals with the exponential mechanism, which is a fundamental tool of Differential Privacy (DP). DP is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses functional data analysis, shape analysis, and nonparametric statistics, which are topics in data science (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions privacy-preserving mechanisms (cs.CR) and simulations (cs.SI).
